[1] Nigeria (Bayelsa)
Date: Thu 18 Sep 2014
Source: Leadership [summ., edited]
http://leadership.ng/news/384349/18-polio-9-measles-cases-reported-bayelsa


9 Measles Cases Reported in Bayelsa State
-----------------------------------------
There was uneasy silence in the Bayelsa State capital following the announcement by the Disease Surveillance and Notification Unit (DSN) of Yenagoa local government area of the State that 18 polio-related cases have been reported in the council within the last 8 months.

According to the announcement, 18 cases of the acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) were reported within the 15 wards of the Yenagoa local government area. An officer attached to the Disease Surveillance and Notification Unit (DSN) reported that 9 suspected measles cases and 3 of neonatal tetanus were also reported within this period. He described the disease outbreak as a "threat" to society and maintained that DSN was committed to check any disease endemic and promoting quality health in the local government.

[Byline: Osa Okhomina]

