[2] Philippines (Central Visayas)
Date: Tue 16 Sep 2014
Source: Manila Bulletin [edited]
http://www.mb.com.ph/measles-cases-in-central-visayas-up-a-whopping-1260/


Measles cases in Central Visayas up a whopping 1260
---------------------------------------------------
Measles cases in Central Visayas from January to 13 Sep of this year [2014] reached 1387 with 7 deaths, or 1260 percent higher than the same period last year [2013], the Department of Health (DOH) in Region VII (DOH-7) said yesterday [15 Sep 2014]. Last year, only 102 measles cases were recorded for the entire Central Visayas region with no fatalities, according to records released by the DOH's Regional Epidemiology Surveillance Unit 7 (RESU-7).

RESU-7 medical chief Dr. Dino Caing said the rise in the number of measles cases in the region can be attributed to the different calamities that struck Cebu, Bohol and Leyte late last year [2013]. This year [2014], Cebu City has the most number of measles cases with 508 and one death, followed by Talisay City with 70 cases and one death. Cases were also recorded in Naga, Argao, Sibonga, San Fernando, and San Francisco in Camotes Island.

The rise in the number of measles cases in Cebu was also due to the coming in of calamity victims into Cebu from Bohol, Leyte and other affected areas. Dr. Caing reiterated the DOH's call for parents to immediately bring their kids, aged 5 and below, to the nearest health centers for measles immunisation. He also urged parents or guardians of children that manifest signs of measles to immediately rush the patient to the hospital or health centers for immediate medical assistance.

[Byline: Mars W. Mosqueda Jr.]

